President Obama has appointed Douglas M. Brooks as the Director of the White House Office of National AIDS Policy (ONAP). Brooks, a leading HIV/AIDS policy expert, will be responsible for reducing new HIV infections, improving health outcomes for people living with HIV, and eliminating HIV health disparities in the United States. ONAP coordinates the implementation of the National HIV/AIDS Strategy and the HIV Care Continuum initiative. It also works with international bodies to ensure America's response to the global pandemic is integrated with prevention, care, and treatment efforts worldwide. Brooks, who is living with HIV, has extensive experience in the field and has served as a consultant to governments and NGOs. He holds a Master of Social Work degree from Boston University and is a licensed clinical social worker.